value.0: Ahh the other clans... which would you care to know about.

If one chooses improperly, one can at least uphold one's error with dignity. The Ventrue embody much that is noble about the Damned, and so, when the time to destroy them comes, we will allow them to die the long way, with honor

They wished for immortality; now they have it. Realize, upstarts, that agony properly administered can make an instant seem like an eternity, and that an eternity of eternities is a long time in which to suffer
So lovely, so pliable, like dolls! Their most charming gift, though, is in the screaming.
No one merits fiercer punishment than the uninvited guest.
No matter how one twists, they always return to their original state. Fascinating.
The aphorism that genius and madness lie close at hand was assuredly coined by a Lunatic wretch who wished to concoct an excuse for his infirmity.
They are shadows in truth - menacing but ultimately ephemeral. Still, oftentimes it is easier to accomplish tasks under cover of cloaking darkness.
Already the hunting hound paces its kennel.. Soon it shall come and lick the feet of its old master.
A worm, some say, can be cut in two, or even minced, yet each piece will wondrously grow whole once more. Can the Setites do likewise, I wonder?
Like ourselves, they have been unjustly toppled. Unlike ourselves, they have not adapted well at all.
Once again the Turks howl outside the gates. The Final Nights must surely be nigh.
Despite our pride in our heritage and customs, little organization exists among us as a clan. Sires and childer remain closer than most, but in general each Fiend makes her own way in the world

We are inexplicably tied to the land, either of our birth or Embrace. When we sleep, we must surround ourself with at least two handfuls of earth from a land important to us as a mortal (the land of your birth, the soil of your demesne, the earth of your grave, you get the idea). Failure to do this leaves us weakened, more with each day, until this is rectified by a night's rest in this sacred earth. We are also very territorial about our domains and especially our havens. Extremely brave (or foolish) are those who trespass on a Tzimisce's haven. However, those lucky visitors a Tzimisce invites into his haven are treated like royalty, but expect extreme courtousy in return.

We rarely Embrace capriciously; as the choice of childer reflects on the sire, and thus we choose only those mortals who we feel have the capacity to improve the clan as a whole. "Brilliance" and "insight" are particularly prized; whether a childe's brilliance and insight manifest in scientific theory or serial murder is a trifling distinction.

Celerity is a Discipline that grants vampires supernatural speed and finesse by expending vitae. Presence, the discipline of unnatural attraction and emotional control. This discipline is the ultimate exaltation of the "Power of personality" that many kindred have.Potence is Discipline that grants the vampires supernatural strength.

We are exceedingly private beings, and placing great value on the sanctity of the haven. In fact, the clan has an entire series of elaborate protocols based around hospitality. Guests invited into a Fiend's haven are protected with the host's unlife; trespassers are pursued to the ends of the Earth and punished in gruesome and lingering fashion. Amenities of mortals matter little to the us.
